## 💾 2. Prerequisites & Global Core Dependencies
Ensure your target server node environment satisfies the following minimum structural versions before compiling database patches:
## 2.1 Backend Environment

* PHP: Version 8.1 or higher (with PDO, openssl, and json extensions explicitly enabled).
* Database Engine: MariaDB 10.4+ or MySQL 8.x running a universal utf8mb4_general_ci encoding scheme to guarantee cross-version sorting safety.
* Server Variables: upload_max_filesize = 10M and post_max_size = 12M to accommodate multi-page PDF scan buffers.

